message.content: cs.SE, cs.HC, cs.CY, cs.CR, cs.IR. The paper focuses on the perceptions and attitudes towards peer review in software engineering, which is a core aspect of the cs.SE sub-category. Additionally, the paper touches on issues related to human-computer interaction (cs.HC), cybersecurity (cs.CR), and information retrieval (cs.IR) in the context of peer review. Finally, the paper discusses the need for community efforts to improve peer review, which could fall under the cs.CY sub-category of computer-supported cooperative work.
